President Joe Biden delivered a speech at the Hyatt Regency Capitol Hill in Washington, D.C., expressing his gratitude and support for firefighters. He emphasized the important role firefighters play in society and recounted personal experiences where firefighters had saved his life and the lives of his loved ones. President Biden pledged to advocate for firefighters and address issues such as cancer risks, toxic exposure, and infrastructure improvements. He also discussed his efforts to ensure fair treatment, dignity, and respect for firefighters, including supporting collective bargaining rights and fair taxation. The President concluded by expressing his deep appreciation for the sacrifices made by firefighters and their families.